Text.string: This planet's a crapbucket, agreed? You know what makes it palatable? Drinkin'! You know where you drink stuff? A bar. Problem is, some jabber cut my bar's power. Get it flowin' again, and you get paid.
See, the problem started when I served drinks to a couple a' jabber named Apollo and Artemis, which is a totally normal thing to say when you're a bartender on Eden-6.
Nice! I should probably mention that I built my bar on a jabber matin' site. Or was it a burial ground? Either way, my bad.

Thanks. This bar is all the people of Eden-6 have left. The COV destroyed everything else. Well, we never had schools or hospitals to begin with, but... when you think about it, a bartender's kinda like a teacher, or a doctor. One who gets you drunk.
Head on back to The Witch's Peat, I'll whip up a few signature cocktails!
Damn it! That other crapflinger Artemis got into the bar and crapped the place up! Kick her out!
Way to kick some drunk monkey butt! It'll be a while before I can reopen The Witch's Peat, but when I do, you get drinks for life. Naw, scratch that. A week. You earned it.
Bottoms up! It's the end of the world somewhere.

But Apollo and Artemis got a taste for my signature cocktails and went apeshit when I cut 'em off. Started flinging their crap all over the bar. After I kicked 'em out, they wrecked the generator and we lost power!

Welcome to The Witch's Peat! As you can see, I still got a little jabber infestation on my hands. Kill 'em before this whole planet sobers up and realizes Eden-6 is an ingrown hair on the ass of life.
Fun fact, “Ass of Life” is also a signature drink at the bar. One part viko berry, one part bog wine. Drink up! And don't forget to plug your nose.
That's Apollo! One of the jabber who killed the bar's power. Put his lights out, will ya?
A damn valve? That's why we got no power! I knew those crap-flingers were sabotaging the bar! Grab it.
We gotta get the generator runnin'. No one likes to drink in the dark. Except ugly people. And people who don't mind hookin' up with ugly people.
“Drink in the Dark” is also one of my signature cocktails. A dash of bogwater, two glugs of stillswill and you'll go temporarily blind! Guaranteed.
Time to get the bar's lights back on! Flip on the breakers.
